layout.p:
Columns: 1 2;
                                                  ruled lines: 14 51;
                                                  written lines: 12 49; Non-uniform layout, with varying number of lines a page.Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.Initial words written in larger characters. Some letters written in red ink (see folios 127v-135r).Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable.Most of the margins are occupied with the commentary. The left margin left for commentary by the scribe has also in some cases been cut away (e.g., folios 86, 97-98).Censor's erasures, e.g., folios 30v, 38r.
